22/08/2010
ZAGREB, Croatia -- A Croat convicted of smuggling 557kg of cocaine has been arrested in Peru, HINA news agency reported on Friday (August 20th), quoting interior ministry sources. Slobodan Kasic, 68, was detained in Lima based on an international arrest warrant. In 2001, he was sentenced in absentia to 13 years in prison for drug smuggling. The cocaine was found in 1997 on a ship that sailed from Ecuador to Rijeka port. Kasic has denied any involvement. Croatia is preparing an extradition request. (HRT, HINA, Croatian Times - 20/08/10) 
